# Designing the Input
Wow, that was way faster than when we added queries! All the heavy lifting we did in the first 3 parts of this series is starting to pay off.

Now that our server allows clients to create messages, we can build that functionality into our React Native client. First, well start by creating a new component `MessageInput` where our users will be able to input their messages.

