# Subscriptions-Transport-WS Authentication
Luckily for us, `SubscriptionClient` has a nifty little feature that lets us lazily (on-demand) connect to our WebSocket by setting `lazy: true`. This flag means we will only try to connect the WebSocket when we make our first subscription call, which only happens in our app once the user is authenticated. When we make our connection call, we can pass the JWT credentials via `connectionParams`. When the user logs out, well close the connection and lazily reconnect when a user log back in and resubscribes.

